<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd">
<en-note><div>MariaDB 10.2 on FreeBSD Server</div><div><br/></div><div><b><u>Install the MariaDB  from the Ports</u></b> </div><div>=&gt; cd /usr/ports/databases/mariadb102-server</div><div>=&gt; sudo make</div><div>=&gt; sudo make install</div><div># Add the line in the “<b>/etc/rc.conf</b> ” : <font color="#941100">mysql_enable</font>=“<font color="#009193">YES</font>&quot;</div><div><br/></div><div><b><u>The MariaDB Server Configuration Files</u></b></div><div><br/></div><div>The example files are located in the “/usr/local/share/mysql/“:</div><div><span><font color="#919191">-rw-r--r--  1 root  wheel   4898 Jul  2 01:56 /usr/local/share/mysql/my-huge.cnf</font></span></div><div><span><font color="#919191">-rw-r--r--  1 root  wheel  20421 Jul  2 01:56 /usr/local/share/mysql/my-innodb-heavy-4G.cnf</font></span></div><div><span><font color="#919191">-rw-r--r--  1 root  wheel   4885 Jul  2 01:56 /usr/local/share/mysql/my-large.cnf</font></span></div><div><span><font color="#919191">-rw-r--r--  1 root  wheel   4898 Jul  2 01:56 /usr/local/share/mysql/my-medium.cnf</font></span></div><div><span><font color="#919191">-rw-r--r--  1 root  wheel   2824 Jul  2 01:56 /usr/local/share/mysql/my-small.cnf</font></span></div><div><span>( I use the medium sized server)</span></div><div>=&gt;<b> sudo cp</b><font color="#941100"> /usr/local/share/mysql/my-medium.cnf</font> <font color="#005493">/usr/local/etc/my.cnf</font></div><div># To allow access from outside, I added the following line in the “<font color="#005493">/usr/local/etc/my.cn</font>f” file:</div><div><font color="#941100">bind-address</font>  =<font color="#009193"> 192.168.100.150</font>  <font color="#5e5e5e"># My server IP Address 192.168.100.150 and the port 3306</font></div><div><br/></div><div><b><u>Starting and Stopping the Server</u></b></div><div>=&gt;<b> sudo</b>  <b>service</b> <font color="#0433ff">mysql-server</font><font color="#4f8f00"> start </font>| <font color="#ff2600">stop</font></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> sudo</span><font color="#941100"> /usr/local/etc/rc.d/</font><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">mysql-server</span> <span style="color: rgb(79, 143, 0);">start</span><span style="color: rgb(94, 94, 94);"> </span><span style="color: rgb(79, 143, 0);"> </span><span style="color: rgb(94, 94, 94);">| </span><font color="#ff2600">stop</font><span style="color: rgb(94, 94, 94);">    # the old way</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(94, 94, 94);"><br/></span></div><div><b><u>To check the Server Status</u></b></div><div>=&gt; <b>service mysql-server</b> <font color="#531b93">status</font></div><div>=&gt;<b> netstat -an | grep</b> 3306</div><div><br/></div><div><b><u>How Set  the  Root password</u></b></div><div><font color="#797979">Note: The default password is empty !</font></div><div>There are two ways to change the password:</div><ol start="1"><li>Recommended way. This command will also give you the option of removing the test databases and anonymous user created by default.</li></ol><div><span>    </span>=&gt;<b> sudo</b> <font style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/usr/local/bin/</font><b>mysql_secure_installation</b><br/></div><div><b><br/></b></div><div><ol start="2"><li>=&gt;<b> sudo</b> <font color="#941100">/usr/local/bin/</font><b>mysqladmin</b> <font color="#0433ff">-u</font><font color="#ff2600"> root</font> <font color="#0433ff">password</font> H***3</li></ol><div><br/></div><div><ol start="3"><li>=&gt;<b> sudo</b> mysql -u root -p &lt;Enter&gt;</li></ol><div>       <b>mysql&gt; </b><font color="#0433ff">UPDATE</font> <font color="#9437ff">user</font> <font color="#0433ff">SET</font> <font color="#9437ff">Password=</font>‘H***3’ <font color="#0433ff">WHERE</font> <font color="#9437ff">User=</font>‘<b>root</b>’;<br/></div></div><div>       <b>mysql&gt;</b> <font color="#0433ff">FLUSH PRIVILEGES</font>;<br/></div><div><span>       <b>mysql&gt;</b> <font color="#0433ff">QUIT</font>;<br/></span></div><div><span><span><span><br/></span></span></span></div><div><span><span><span>How To Create a User and Give full privileges</span></span></span></div><div><span><span><span><br/></span></span></span></div><div>=&gt;<b> mysql</b> <font color="#941100">-u</font><font color="#ff2600"> root</font> <font color="#941100">-p</font>                  </div><div>=&gt;<b> show</b> <font color="#009051">databases</font>;                <font color="#797979">  # Show available databases</font></div><div><span>=&gt; <b>use</b> <font color="#009051">mysql</font>;    <span>    <span>    <span>    <span>    <span>       <font color="#797979"> # Switch to the mysql database</font></span></span></span></span></span></span></div><div>=&gt;<font color="#941100"> </font><font color="#0433ff">CREATE</font><b> User</b> khasanov;     <font color="#797979"> # Create the user khasanov</font></div><div>=&gt;<font color="#0433ff"> SELECT</font><b> Use</b>r <font color="#0433ff">FROM</font><font color="#941100"> user</font>;   <font color="#797979"># Show the users in the</font><font color="#945200"> user</font><font color="#797979"> Table</font> </div><div><span><span><span><font color="#919191"><br/></font></span></span></span></div><div><span><span><span><font color="#919191"># To grant all the privileges to the all databases for the user khasanov at localhost (127.0.0.1):</font></span></span></span></div><div>=&gt;<font color="#0433ff"> GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON</font> <b>*.*</b><font color="#0433ff"> TO</font> ‘<b>khasanov</b>’<b>@</b>‘<b>localhost</b>’ <font color="#0433ff">IDENTIFIED BY</font> ‘Hydrogen3’;</div><div>=&gt; <font color="#0433ff">FLUSH PRIVILEGES</font>;</div></div><div><br/></div><div><font color="#919191"># To see the privileges for the user khasanov:</font></div><div>=&gt; <font color="#0433ff">SHOW GRANTS FOR</font> <b>‘khasanov’@‘localhost’</b>;</div><div><br/></div><div><font color="#797979"># To allow the user “khasanov” remote login from IP = 192.168.100.100</font></div><div> =&gt;<span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);"> GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">*.*</span><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);"> TO</span> ‘<span style="font-weight: bold;">khasanov</span>’<span style="font-weight: bold;">@</span>‘<b>192.168.100.100</b>’ <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">IDENTIFIED BY</span> ‘Hydrogen3’;</div><div>=&gt; <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">FLUSH PRIVILEGES</span>;</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);"># To allow the user “khasanov” remote login from ANY IP ADDRESS:</span></div><div> =&gt;<span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);"> GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON</span> <span style="font-weight: bold;">*.*</span><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);"> TO</span> ‘<span style="font-weight: bold;">khasanov</span>’<span style="font-weight: bold;">@</span>‘<b>%</b>’ <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">IDENTIFIED BY</span> ‘Hydrogen3’;</div><div>=&gt; <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">FLUSH PRIVILEGES</span>;</div><div><br/></div></en-note>
